From 8743e2d661540d08a6f8f97b4072222a94f81479 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Christian Hewitt <christianshewitt@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 13 Feb 2026 08:07:46 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 50/94] WIP: media: meson: vdec: fix NULL pointer dereference
 in vdec_start_streaming

When a codec that does not implement the .resume callback (e.g.
codec_mpeg12) undergoes a capture queue restart due to a source change
event, vdec_start_streaming() unconditionally calls codec_ops->resume()
which results in a NULL pointer dereference and kernel oops.

This occurs because the REINIT_ALWAYS V4L2 M2M quirk forces a
resolution renegotiation that stops and restarts the capture queue,
setting sess->status to STATUS_NEEDS_RESUME. On the subsequent
VIDIOC_STREAMON the resume path is taken but codec_mpeg12_ops does
not define .resume (only H.264, HEVC, and VP9 do).

Add a NULL check before calling codec_ops->resume(), consistent with
how codec_ops->drain is already guarded elsewhere in the same file.
The session status is still transitioned to STATUS_RUNNING so the
codec can continue operating normally.

Fixes: 876f123b6595 ("media: meson: vdec: add support for MPEG1 and MPEG2")
Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Signed-off-by: Christian Hewitt <christianshewitt@gmail.com>
---
 drivers/staging/media/meson/vdec/vdec.c | 3 ++-
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/staging/media/meson/vdec/vdec.c b/drivers/staging/media/meson/vdec/vdec.c
index 91247810a1b9..93f5beaeb51e 100644
--- a/drivers/staging/media/meson/vdec/vdec.c
+++ b/drivers/staging/media/meson/vdec/vdec.c
@@ -302,7 +302,8 @@ static int vdec_start_streaming(struct vb2_queue *q, unsigned int count)
 	if (sess->status == STATUS_NEEDS_RESUME &&
 	    q->type == V4L2_BUF_TYPE_VIDEO_CAPTURE_MPLANE &&
 	    sess->changed_format) {
-		codec_ops->resume(sess);
+		if (codec_ops->resume)
+			codec_ops->resume(sess);
 		sess->status = STATUS_RUNNING;
 		return 0;
 	}
